Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The highly anticipated KwaZulu-Natal ANC elective conference set for this weekend has been postponed. The conference will take place between 22-24 July. READ: KZN ANC regional and league leaders meet with Zuma Several provincial leaders are set to contest the chair position held by Premier Sihle Zikalala, who is seeking re-election. The party held a Provincial Executive Committee in Durban on Monday ahead of that conference next weekend.